HEADWORD: higher-up
<hw>high"er-up"</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A superior officer or official;
a person having greater rank or station or quality than others; -- used
chiefly in <pluf>pl.</pluf></def> <mark>[Slang]</mark>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> superior, superordinate.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source> + <source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Higher thought</ent>⟦br⟧
